entry.title: [DevTools] Do not trust TextEncoding of non-text resources
entry.content:
In NetworkResourcesData, we store text encoding coming over

the network to later use in "Network.getResponseBody"

and similar protocol methods.



However, ResourceResponse may come with some arbitrary encoding

(e.g. charset=utf-8), even though it's actually binary data.

Depending on the actual resource type, the encoding may be ignored

in Blink (for example, in font resources), and everything works

as expected despite the suspicious charset.



We should not blindly transfer such resources as text in

DevTools protocol to avoid data corruption, and instead encode them

as base64.



Drive-by: remove NetworkResourcesData::ResourceData::buffer_

since it is always nullptr.

entry.title: content: Dispatch pending event callbacks during InputHandler teardown
entry.content:
With RenderDocument, we destroy the CompositorThreadEventQueue as a

part of detaching the InputHandler so the compositor can be reattached

to the new widget. Since this happens before the WidgetInputHandler

mojo connection is reset in the renderer, it triggers an assert that

there are no pending DispatchEventCallbacks associated with the mojo

interface.



Fix that by explicitly invoking the pending callbacks with an empty

result when the CompositorThreadEventQueue is destroyed. This is correct

because the old Widget will be destroyed immediately after the swap

finishes.

entry.title: Call PreloadingAttempt::SetFailureReason for kPrefetchNotUsedProbeFailed
entry.content:
When probe fails, failure is set

(`PreloadingTriggeringOutcome::kFailure` and

`PrefetchStatus::kPrefetchNotUsedProbeFailed`)



- To `PrefetchContainer::prefetch_status_`

(and thus to `PrefetchProxy.PrefetchedResource` metrics),

- To `devtools_instrumentation::DidUpdatePrefetchStatus()`,

- But not to `PreloadingAttempt`.



This CL sets the failure also to `PreloadingAttempt`,

so that the metrics/DevTools are consistent for

entry.title: TestUdpEchoServer now creates a server socket via the network service.
entry.content:
This CL modifies how the TestUdpEchoServer sets up the server.

Previously, the server directly created a net::UDPServerSocket and set

up a loop to wait for reads and echo the message.



Now, the server goes through the network service and creates a

network::mojom::UDPSocket. This is necessary for the tests that

use this server to pass on Windows with the network service sandbox

enabled, as otherwise the sandbox blocks reads/writes to the server

socket and the tests time out.



The tests that use the TestUdpEchoServer still behave the same way.

entry.title: Add async initialization to net::CookieCryptoDelegate interface.
entry.content:
This CL adds a new 'Init' method to the CookieCryptoDelegate. The

method is called during initialization and before any encryption or

decryption is performed.



The SQLitePersistentCookieStore::Backend is updated to call

this when Load or LoadCookiesForKey is called, before

scheduling the DB task to the background task runner, if a delegate

has been supplied during construction.



The existing implementation of CookieCryptoDelegate in

components/cookie_config is updated to simply call the callback

immediately via a direct call, meaning there is *no functionality

change intended by this CL*.



However, the tests are augmented to supply a more complex

implementation that posts a delayed callback task to replicate

future behavior where Init will (sometimes) be truly async.



A few tests are updated as a result of this:



1. Load and Flush methods are changed to a more modern pattern

using nested task runners rather than a bespoke

base::WaitableEvent. This ensures that any tasks running on

the client thread can execute waiting for the completion

callbacks.



2. SQLitePersistentCookieStoreTest.Coalescing is updated to

destroy the store and wait for destruction before creating

a new store. Without this, the background thread is not

drained and the object can end up going out of scope before

the next iteration of the loop begins and the tasks on

the (now freed) background task runner execute.



3. SQLitePersistentCookieStoreTest.KeyInconsistency opts into

encryption, so as to fully test the async path, as it also

relies on some subtle internal behavior of the Backend.



4. SQLitePersistentCookieStoreTest.TestLoadCookiesForKey queues

tasks directly to the background task runner in a very

particular order during the test, in order to verify that

LoadCookiesForKey calls can complete before Load calls, when

the background task runner is blocked.

Since the background task was not being queued by the Backend

until after the CookieCryptoDelegate had been initialized, this

meant that the order of tasks queued (by the test) onto the

background task runner was no longer consistent with what the

test intends to verify. To fix this, the cookie crypto delegate

is fully initialized before the final blocking task is posted

by the test onto the background thread. This preserves the

existing task ordering expected by the test.



BUG=1500086

entry.title: [CrOS Cellular] Check connectivity before refresh profile list
entry.content:
The current managed cellular installation order is: 1. check cellular

device 2. check euicc presence 3. refresh profile list 4. check non

cellular connectivity 5. check shill config 6 perform installation.

The problem here is if user happens to turn on hotspot while the managed

profile installation happens, the refresh profile list will make

cellular connection disconnect and thus tear down the hotspot.

In order to fix the issue, we can make check non-cellular connectivity

before refresh profile list since using hotspot has to turn off Wifi.

entry.title: Apply Latin-ASCII transliteration for address comparison.
entry.content:
We did not consider 'Str.' and 'Straße' as equivalent in German

addresses because our normalization rules contained a "strasse" ->

"str" rule and no "straße" -> "str" rule. The ß was not transliterated

for the comparison.



Similarly the street name "Iłłakowiczówny" and "Illakowiczowny" were

not considered equivalent because "ł" is not a composition of a letter

and a nonspacing mark (diacritic).



These problems are fixed with the CL.



It remains to introduce German transliteration for umlauts (ü -> ue)

for addresses from German speaking countries.

entry.title: Modify sequence local storage so that ComPtrs can be used with it.
entry.content:
With https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4957333,

a call to & on the template parameter T was added. This made it so that

if a ComPtr is stored in a SequenceLocalStorageSlot, it would get

released automatically upon the first read.



The root cause is that ComPtr has an operator override for &

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/cppcx/wrl/comptr-class?view=msvc-170#operator-ampersand

calling & releases the interface associated with the ComPtr.



Since ComPtr is common on windows and root causing bugs from this is

challenging, this change fixes SequenceLocalStorageSlot to avoid

calling & on the template and instead use std::addressof.

entry.title: TaskAttribution: Ensure CPED is cleared for upcoming per-Isolate CPED
entry.content:
[Get|Set]ContinuationPreservedEmbedderData is being refactored to store

CPED on the isolate rather than the context in v8. But without changing

blink to use the new API, we can have a situation where resetting the

CPED when a task scope is destroyed fails if the context is gone (e.g.

detached frame). Previously this wasn't a problem because the data was

stored on the context, but with per-isolate CPED, this can leak the

context / propagate wrong values.



This CL works around this by clearing the utility context's CPED. With

per-Context CPED, this essentially does nothing, but when the

per-Isolate CPED v8 changes land, this will clear the per-Isolate data.



Note: this is only temporary and will be removed once the v8 changes

land, in favor of using the new API.
